      "writtenOn": "2019-07-26T18:32:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is (temporary) ownership transfer in SkShaper, so that precludes the non-sk_sp approach.\n\nI lean toward const sk_sp\u003c\u003e\u0026 just because at the SkottieShaper interface level there is no semantic ownership transfer: users are simply calling a static function, and SkShaper grabbing a ref under the hood feels like an implementation detail (we may refactor SkShaper to never grab a ref at some point, in which case prematurely grabbing one upstack is counterproductive).\n\n(note that we use the same pattern for other interfaces, e.g. SkCanvas::{drawTextBlob,drawPicture})\n\nI don\u0027t feel strongly about it though, going to refactor as soon as I get the darn test passing on nativefont bots :)",
      "parentUuid": "d3814ed9_1bd5ebf3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 24,
